## Net Dust Runtime (ndr)

The Net Dust Runtime (ndr) Installation is possible
By default, a standard installation of the runtime does not include the standard (`std.`) library, keeping the core engine minimal and lightweight.

> [!NOTE]
> **Standard Library Requirement:**
> While the **Net Dust Runtime itself** installs successfully, the **standard library (`std.`)** is not present by default. To utilize full language features and core functionalities, it must be installed separately.

### Recommendations

- Install the `std.` library directly from the official NetDust repository.
- Verify your environment paths once the standard library installation is complete.
